      "writtenOn": "2019-10-03T00:33:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Seems like there\u0027s a race condition / deadlock here:\nt1: goroutine A calls NewTaskCache, which creates mod :\u003d ModifiedTasksCh and starts goroutine B\nt2: goroutine B reads first item from mod\nt3: goroutine B checks for c.onModFn, sees it\u0027s nil\nt4: goroutine A calls c.OnModifiedTasks to set c.onModFn\nindefinitely:\n  - goroutine A waits for onModFn to be called (to continue past \u003c-wait)\n  - goroutine B waits for new modified tasks to be returned on mod\n\nISTM the only way to make this work would be to pass the onModFn to NewTaskCache. (IMO that has the added benefit that you can remove OnModifiedTasks, given later comments. Maybe we\u0027d need to add it back someday, but I\u0027ll worry about that when it comes up.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 58,
        "endChar": 7
      },
